<Project Sdk="Microsoft.NET.Sdk">

	<PropertyGroup>
		<Nullable>enable</Nullable>
		<IsPackable>true</IsPackable>
		<IsTrimmable>false</IsTrimmable>
		<OutputType>Library</OutputType>
		<Deterministic>true</Deterministic>
		<AllowUnsafeBlocks>true</AllowUnsafeBlocks>
		<DisableImplicitMicrosoftCSharpReference>true</DisableImplicitMicrosoftCSharpReference>

		<Description><![CDATA[
Nalix.Network is the high-performance networking runtime for the Nalix ecosystem. It provides TCP and UDP listeners, connection management, packet dispatch, protocol lifecycle orchestration, middleware integration, and adaptive throttling for building scalable distributed services.

Designed for latency-sensitive workloads, it emphasizes efficient I/O, predictable concurrency, observability, and secure transport behavior so applications can process real-time traffic reliably under sustained load.
		]]></Description>

		<PackageReleaseNotes><![CDATA[
- Expanded ConnectionHub observability with configurable shard telemetry, anonymous queue depth metrics, and capacity-related runtime hooks.
- Improved packet dispatch diagnostics with clearer loop, semaphore, and middleware instrumentation reporting.
- Hardened UDP listener authentication with timestamp validation, Poly1305-based integrity checks, and replay-guard protections.
- Added adaptive throttling primitives including ConnectionLimiter, TokenBucketLimiter, and PolicyRateLimiter.
- Enhanced protocol lifecycle and metrics infrastructure for more reliable service orchestration.
- Improved timing and scheduling components with high-resolution wheel-based coordination and synchronization helpers.
- Continued performance, stability, and maintainability refinements across the networking stack.
		]]></PackageReleaseNotes>

	</PropertyGroup>

	<Import Project="..\Nalix.Build.props" />
	<Import Project="..\Package.Build.props" />

	<ItemGroup>
		<ProjectReference Include="..\Nalix.Common\Nalix.Common.csproj" />
		<ProjectReference Include="..\Nalix.Framework\Nalix.Framework.csproj" />
	</ItemGroup>
</Project>
